Ahahaha. Ok. I'm done.

So, first, Happy Birthday ! Hope you had... have. A good one. Whichever. Onwards! It is now, Tuesday! Basically 7 days after my birthday. For my birthday, I got chocolate, more Matter things, a massive body pillow (I swear, body pillows are better then regular pillows) and a fan. There might've been more, but remembering now is about as possible as getting me to be nice after being asked a really stupid question. That was Friday. Now, before I go onto Saturday, I had decided at the beginning of this month that I was going to get myself a birthday present. Something no one else could get me, because I thought of it first, and therefore, it was mine to spend my money on. So, on Saturday, after spending two weeks arguing with people, telling people off and generally ignoring some of the general comments from the people I associate with, I got my tattoo done. I will say this though, for all of you pansies who have gotten a tattoo and bitched for hours that it hurt, you're either bluffing like hell or cry from paper cuts. That, did not hurt. Several hours later, when everything settled down and the damn thing started to scab, that started to get irritating. So, yes, I will post a picture at the end of all this. It's on my left shoulder, back. Well, tehcnically I was supposed to get it in the center of my back, but, pfft, since when do I ever do things exactly as I plan them?! Seriously. So I spent Sunday sitting around doing nothing, because I have to wear a tank top or risk getting polysporin all over everything. And at minus anything degrees, you do not want to go out in a tank top. Monday, I went to my parents and dominated the television, but once more, I did absolutely fuck all. Today, I got my present from my parents. A DVD Player. Which, seriously rocks. Now, I am no longer trapped watching everything on my computer. If I have to run all my stupid scans to figure out what the hell is going on with this crappy piece of worthlessness, I'm not stuck having to leave the appartment. Which, is a win. My younger sisters are still pestering my parents for the chance to go buy my presents, since they were not able to before. This, amuses me, but it does mean there is the chance of me posting once more this week. Even higher chance of me posting is if I finally get some fucking cheesecake. I want cheesecake. I, am bored now. So, yes, photo.
There, now. Toodles. xx

So, first thing, I am now, Twenty-Two years old! I have no idea why, but for no real reason I have been beside myself with happiness. I mean, completely estatic. There is of course the argueable case that I have lost my mind, and, if I have, I am enjoying every minute of it.

I may have to kill anyone who attempts to return it.

Anyway, other news is school related. Why is this important? Because last month, early, I took 5 exams in 2 days. While the official marks are still being waited for, the teaher who was in charge of the exam was informed of who passed and who didn't. Seriously? Happiness news -ever-!

If you didn't guess, I passed!

Yes, so my birthday celebration is tomorrow, because then my mother has the day off. I think she was ready to blow when she discovered that she had work on my birthday, but it is all good. I mean, at least this year she remembered to wish me a good one. It may have been in the -20's for the past few days, but, I think I've been happier in this past week then I ever have.

And, on the recond, why the hell didn;t anyone tell me about the sarcasm in Supernatural?! I am completely addicted. Sam, he's my favourite. He's totally the most adorable thing you will ever lay eyes upon! The episode about the cursed rabbit's foot? Totally my favourite right now.

xx

To everyone on my f-list, and to anyone who wanders past, Merry Christmas if you don't celebrate, just happy holidays/winter vacation.
...there, my christmas cheer has been delivered. Leave me alone until next year. ;)

So, I have discovered that I am rather impatient, and if you push too hard, my temper comes into play. My sister seems to lack the knowledge to realize that when I start just pissy, that she should just shut the hell up. I mean, there is no logic behind forcing yourself to endure three hours of waiting, when you can go home and force someone to drive you the next day. Especially when it's a damn school thing. There are teachers, they all drive to school, eventually someone has to put the effort into helping. But for reasons that escape me, my sister believes she has to do everything on her on. I may have made her cry, which I feel bad about, but I do not regret anything I said, because it was all true. Christmas Part or not, tomorrow is going to be a hell of a rush, adding one item to the list would probably not effect a thing.

Right, anyway. So, I did all those presentations. We have people still bugging us about how to fold a proper origami star (and I'll kick your ass if you ask. If you wanna know, go look it up on YouTube.) It was awesome. We had a plot and story and costumes. I think we were actually the most enthusiastic pair out of all four groups. I mean, we had costumes. Can you imagine how many people must've thought we were out of our minds? The teacher was sure we would scare people.

And we probably did.

I have two more days of school until either May/June or next September. Depends, really, because I hate the new teachers they have. Honestly, why is it that when a teacher is replaced in the school, three others are replaced, and everything just goes to hell? It sucks, epic fail.

I have another rant. Why the hell do people bother posting their stories then friend locking them? There is no fucking logic behind this. I don't want to add a complete stranger to my fucking livejournal, just so I might be added to their journal so I might be able to read the entire story, especially if I have never read it before. I seriously hate that. Even worse is when you read a story and their tell you it'll be locked, and if you want to read it, you have to add them. I mean, seriously, what the hell? Isn't the entire point to a friends lock is to make it all friends only? Like...what?! What a fucking rip off. I think people who friend lock their stories shouldn't be allowed to post in communities. Talk about a massive let down.

Meh.

I have ranted, and now? I feel a bit better.

I am still going to hurt someone.

So, today I did a presentation for my creativity class. I dragged Karl from his warm comfy bed and made him drag his ass over to the school for the sole purpose of borrowing his laptop. And before I continue, I must admit I had a fanbitch moment. It loaded PS CS3 Extended in less then a minute. And Worked smoothly the entire time, I was like, swooning. I was also secretly plotting to steal it. Anyway, back to the original topic. I thought for certain that when I started the project, no one was going to remain awake. It is really boring when I first start, because it looks nothing like the finished product. Nothing, at all. It was hilarious. But as I progressed I actually got a bunch of 'ooo's. I was disturbed. Yes, right, topic. So I finished, at least, I thought I had, until someone pointed out that I had forgotten the -bubbles-. Picky little annoyances. ...You know, I never explained what the presentation was. Ahaha, oops? Right, I had to do a personal project, something that was not allowed to be worked on in school. I designed two posters for the class and was asked, for a week, how I did it. So, I set up a day where I showed them. Of course, I am rather certain I missed a good 7 steps, but its all good. On Monday, I do a dry run of the second set of presentations I must do. My partner and I have chosen to wing it, just to see if we make anyone laugh so hard they cry. If no one does, we will drown ourselves in cupcakes. Right after we steal them from the people doing cupcake decorations. Wednesday and Thursday I start classes at 9:30am and finished at 3:30am. Wait...wait. Not classes. exams Yes, I have twelve hours of exams stretched over two days. I am ready to cumbust. Friday should be an easy day at school, Monday the 8th, there is no school and then Wednesday? Presentations for the entire school. Excuse me while I flee in terror. Onwards! I have made the fascinating discovery that if you actually talk to other people and listen to them, this makes -conversation-. Even better? I have discovered I know more sarcastic people then I ever thought I would. It's all good times at school these days. Bad jokes with heavy sarcasm and over-reacting. How could anything make it better? Add chocolate. I've spent more time laughing int he last month, then I have the last 6 months combined. I am like, in heaven. If there is a comeback for a comment, it will be said, even if it gets killed. Its bloody fucking brilliant. Wednesday? Yeah, laughed so hard I needed to take Tylenol and Advil for my ribs. Win much? I probably have more to add, but I am tired of rambling, and seriously, there are epople to exchange bad ideas with. Toodles.

So, the school year has officially started. Has been since the 2nd. And, I can say with absolute certainty, I hate the temporairy French Teacher. I dropped French class after the third class when I was accused of swearing. I really hate being accused of things I didn't do. Additionally this teacher has threatened people if they speak English in her class. Yes, I consider being told to stand before the class and sing, in French, a threat. That humiliating, and man does it aggravate me in ways that had people listening in amusement as I swore solidily for an entire class.

So yeah, no more French. Couldn't even bribe me backw ith that woman teaching. I take English and Creativity. I have to finish two papers and lead a discussion before I can do the first half of the exams. Sadly, this means I have to think of a topic to lead a discussion on. Any suggestions?

Creativity is kind of amusing. As this is my third time doing the exam, it is pretty much set and sold that I'm going to aggravate the teacher. And probably a few of my fellow classmates. Luckily, this is the only class where talking is encouraged. So we're all cracked jokes from 9:30 to 10:30 in the morning.

Ok, now I am bored of school crap. My sister is officially 15 now, which means my youngest sister will be 12 soon. Man, they start getting old. We discovered something hilarious. And yes, I mean hilarious. There are four sisters, and we've managed to mess up the heights. It's second youngest (shortest), youngest, me and second oldest. It's hilarious. Especially when people keep forgetting that Jackie (second oldest) and I are related. Good times there.

There is probably loads of fun stuff, but I'd have to think. Oh, wait, yes. Right now? My bookbag weighs a good 25 pounds. I have 7 HTML books in there for the purpose of doing my research paper. Problem with this? Most my books are badly outdated. Case example? I don't think anyone uses IE4 or Netscape anymore.

It's funny.

Anyway, I am bored of typing now.

I'll try to remember to update before another 2 months pass xD
xx

Meh.

I am officially in my last year of French, but, that's not for two months.

Do I have summer plans? Fuck no.

Do I intend to make any? Ahahaha.

I just wanted to do a happy dance somewhere xD

My tiara is made of barbed wire, wrapping around and sinking into my skull. Clutching to my mind in ways no other ever could. Every piece of sharp digging metal is created from emotions. Happiness pierces the back of my head, painting my hair a rich red. Anger pierces the sides of my head, coating my ears in crimson sadness. Jealous of course drips through my eyes, blinding me from logic. Everything just fills me with this need for release, and release I shall have. Dripping and slipping, blood and tears; I write now to say good-bye in a moment of weakened emotional structure. My words will never be endless and they will forever more be forgotten as the sun sets in the western skies. My actions will be remembered though, for they are truly endless. My actions are what will mould tomorrow into a miserable clay figure filled with hatred and sadness. This is my good-bye, the removal of my tiara. I pass it on, for I know I will be followed into someplace darker.

---------

It was suggested I post this here. I have no idea where it came from, I was just typing.

And, in other news, I've already started on new designed for www.angeredthoughts.com. Why? because I had an idea. Will they get anywhere? Who knows.

That, is all.

Though now I need a title.

So, let's start from the top, shall we? I last posted on... Sunday, I believe. Not bad, not bad, this is probably a record on my behalf. Last post was rater useless, though I suppose it was also a bit of fun, so there you go. righ tnow, I am wavering between pure fury and unimaginable sadness; not entirely sure about the second one. It's just sort of crushing in and clinging desperately to the edges of my mind, making me feel like curling into a tiny ball somewhere and hiding. Oh well, it'll go away, it always does. So, yeah, fury. You know, I detest it when people use my computer, especially when I am not around to monitor them and make sure they don't fuck it up completely. Last time, my harddrive died completely. No, wait, that was the time before, the last time was my motherboard died and my birthday was spent with my mother bitching loudly about the fact she had to dish out the money for me to get a new computer. Pfft, thanks a lot. Now? The monitor I had, that was slowly dying, is dead. Apparently, somethign popped within and my bedroom is now smelling of eletrical fire. Joy. So, now I get the massive joy of waiting to hear if anything can be done about my monitor. And there had bloodyw ell better be, because I can barely tolerate 1024x768, if that's all I am allowed ot deal with afterwards I will, and I repeat, I will go fucking phsychotic. Really. I will. Rusty spoons! Yeah... I've been spetacularly moody in the past few days. Like, record breaking moody. I could probably reduce people to tears with a look right now, I've been so moody. I've been completely uncaring of other people's problems. It's been brilliant. I think I've completely pissed people off to the point. But haha, I win. Not thinking about your problems now, are you? No, I didn't actually mean to be so bitchy to everyone, but I'm allowed to be off, to completely not care about everyone else for awhile. It's mean, I know. Bitchy and rude. But I am gettign better and I am no longer as moody, which means I'll soon be diving head first into a bunch of problems I might have answers to, only to be ignored. You know, that has become a pet peeve. Seriously, if you're going to ask for advice, at least listen to it, weigh the pros and cons of it. Don't just brush it off because it sounds stupid, it's annoying as all hell. Really, it is. Meh. I am compeltely random here, I keep going from here, to my music, to the television screen. Toodles. xx Edit: So yeah, monitor is back, but apparently it now has a blue hue to it and there is a hunt for a new monitor for me about to begin. For some reason, I don't think I'm going to get to go to the PATD concert...
